node.doctext:
(This won't actually hurt them, or take away experience points, but it will make them THINK like they've lost a some).  Don't use it to harass, but tuck it away for a rainy day.  This, like other small stuff, gets old if you use it too much.

[{openform}]
Make user <input type="text" name="user"> think he or she has lost <input type="text" name="amount"><input type="submit" value="do it"><br><br>

[%

  my $usr = $query->param('user');
  my $numxp = $query->param('amount');

  return "We'll need a user and an amount to continue" unless($usr && $numxp);

  $usr = getNode($usr, 'user');

  my $usrvars = getVars($usr);

  if($$usr{user_id} == $$USER{user_id}){
    $$VARS{oldexp} = $$usr{experience} + $numxp;
  }
  else
  {

    $$usrvars{oldexp} = $$usr{experience} + $numxp;

    setVars($usr, $usrvars);

  }

  return "Done."
%]
